ABUJA – Nigeria has recorded two new deaths from the Coronavirus pandemic as the National Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) released its latest report Friday night.It said on its Twitter handle @NCDCgov that deaths occured in Lagos and Edo states. These bring to four the number of deaths resulting from coronavirus in Nigeria. In addition, 20 new cases were confirmed to bring the number of confirmed cases to 210. The report is reproduced below: Twenty new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; 11 in Lagos, 3 in the FCT, 3 in Edo, 2 in Osun & 1 in Ondo Two new deaths have been recorded in Lagos and Edo State As at 10:30 pm 3rd April there are 210 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. https://t.co/YzXdfxXPTe ABUJA - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced 12 new confirmed cases of coronavirus. In its latest report posted on Twitter, NCDC said nine of the news cases were from Osun while Edo and Ekiti states reported two and one respectively. The full tweet reads: Twelve new… April 1, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - President Muhammadu Buhari on Sunday stated that the Federal Government has recruited hundreds of ad-hoc staff to man call centres and support tracing and testing efforts in Lagos and Abuja. Buhari who was addressing the nation about four weeks after the first coronavirus… March 30, 2020 In "News" ABUJA - Nigeria has again recorded eight new cases of coronavirus, also know as Covid-19, bringing the total number to 97. Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, Saturday night announced that Oyo State recorded four new cases while Kaduna has been added to the list. The tweet @NCDCgov reads: “Eight… March 28, 2020 In "News"